{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The clause extractor identifies all key terms (parties, dates, obligations, penalties) present in the contract.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"This is extraction quality, not just wiring. A mock extractor could trivially return expected terms and hide real misses on nuanced legal phrasing. The real failure boundary is the model’s semantic performance on contract text, which can vary by prompt/model behavior.","test_description":"Run the real clause-extractor model on a curated set of real contract snippets with gold-labeled key terms; assert recall/precision thresholds per term type and fail on missed required terms.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.65,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The risk assessor flags language that would be problematic under the configured risk policy, even when the problematic phrasing is indirect or euphemistic.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Detecting indirect/euphemistic risk language is model judgment quality. In-process mocks or rule stubs can pass while the real model fails to infer risk semantics. Correctness depends on real AI classification behavior.","test_description":"Execute the real risk-assessor model against policy-specific legal clauses containing direct and euphemistic risk language; verify expected risk labels/justifications meet acceptance criteria and that euphemistic cases are flagged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The compliance checker correctly determines whether the contract meets all applicable regulatory requirements for the configured jurisdiction.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"The behavior asserts correctness of regulatory determination, which is semantic/legal reasoning quality of the AI reviewer. Mocking the checker would hide misclassification failures on real jurisdictional text.","test_description":"Call the real compliance-checker model with contracts mapped to known jurisdictional compliance outcomes; assert pass/fail determinations and requirement-level findings match labeled ground truth within defined quality thresholds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.7,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"When two reviewers flag the same clause with conflicting assessments, the merge step preserves both assessments with attribution.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic merge logic at a local function/object boundary. Real model calls are not needed to reproduce the conflict-resolution failure; direct structured inputs can expose loss of attribution or overwrite bugs.","test_description":"Invoke the merge function with synthetic reviewer outputs containing the same clause id and conflicting assessments; assert output includes both assessments, correct reviewer attribution, and no silent overwrite.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full pipeline dispatches all three reviewers, collects results, and merges into a unified report without losing any reviewer findings for a real contract.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This spans multiple agentic steps (three real AI reviewers) plus orchestration/merge. Failures can emerge from concurrent dispatch, partial collection, timing, and agent output variability across steps; lower-level tests can miss end-to-end loss or mis-association.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end execution on real contracts using all three real reviewer calls in parallel, then merge; assert each reviewer’s findings are present in the final report with traceable attribution and no dropped/duplicated clauses across repeated runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.6}}]}
